<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-01T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-01T13:00:00-05:00" n="754" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.114 Narcotics/1227: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-01T14:00:00-04:00">August 1, 1935—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>230. Your despatch No. 3648.<note n="99" xml:id="d754fn99">Dated June 26,
                                1935; not printed.</note></p>
                        <list>
                            <label>(1)</label>
                            <item>Report by radio date when new system of narcotic drug import
                                certificates will become effective.</item>
                            <label>(2)</label>
                            <item>Inform all consular offices in China that when new system becomes
                                effective prospective importers who are subject to extraterritorial
                                jurisdiction should continue to transmit through the American Consul
                                the same documentation as heretofore in addition to sending either
                                directly or through the American Consul the Chinese Government’s
                                import permit. Consular officers should inform regular importers
                                from the United States.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>